        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-30T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="845" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24522/11–3045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-30T13:00:00-05:00">November 30, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>695. Reference draft note to Galo Plaza which you carried to Quito. In view of
                    further conversation with Ambassador Plaza in which he again admitted that there
                    had been no “Twenty Million Dollar commitment,” Dept has decided not to send him
                    a note on Galapagos Base question at this time. You should however, use
                    substance of draft in conversations with FoMin should he raise the question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
